Higher Education Minister Blade Nzimande is briefing the country on his recommendations on the 2017 fees adjustments for universities and TVET colleges. Watch live here. This comes as the University of Cape Town suspended the academic programme amid threats of protest action.For several weeks, fee increment increases have been at the vortex of violent upheaval at the University of KwaZulu-Natal, during which time a prized law library was torched.The briefing by Nzimande follows the Council on Higher Education report for 2017 fee adjustments, as well as his &ldquo;ongoing consultations with key stakeholders&rdquo;. &nbsp;The video above was streamed to YouTube by SABC Digital News.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.